UNITED STATES of America, Libelant-Appellee, v. THE British Oil Screw ALGIE, Her Tackle, Apparel, Furniture, Papers and Engines, and Her Cargo Consisting of 10 Bottles of Scotch Whisky and 2,580 Bags of Rye and Scotch Whisky, YARMOUTH SHIPPING COMPANY, Ltd., Claimant-Appellant. No. 59. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 20, 1933. Howard W. Ameli, U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Herbert H. Kellogg and Alfred C. McKenzie, Asst. U. S. Attys., both of Brooklyn, N. Y., of counsel), for libelant. Louis Halle, of New York City (Milton R. Kroopf, of New York City, of counsel),, for appellant.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS K HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree [56 E. (2d) 388] affirmed.
